# Regression: re-registering a migration with the same body+rollback must be a
# no-op (idempotent). The catalog stores a content hash on first sighting; a
# subsequent `CREATE MIGRATION` with matching name and matching hash returns
# the existing row without writing again, so the migration list still contains
# exactly one row for that name.

(admin "CREATE MIGRATION 'm_idem' { CREATE NAMESPACE app_idem }")
(admin "CREATE MIGRATION 'm_idem' { CREATE NAMESPACE app_idem }")
query 'from system::migrations filter { name == "m_idem" } map { name, action, body }'
---
> +----------+-----------+-----------------------------+
> |   name   |  action   |            body             |
> +----------+-----------+-----------------------------+
> |  m_idem  |  Pending  |  CREATE NAMESPACE app_idem  |
> +----------+-----------+-----------------------------+
>
